; Coverage for amount.cc line 490:
; When multiplying a bare amount (no commodity) by a percentage amount,
; the result inherits the "%" commodity. quantity(amount) strips the
; commodity, so the multiplication result takes "%" from the multiplier.

2024/01/01 Test
    Expenses:Food    100.00
    Assets:Cash

test reg --format "%(quantity(amount) * 50%)\n"
50%
-50%
end test
